text.section:
"Chief executive officer" means:
for Baltimore City, the Mayor;
for a charter county, the county executive or, if there is no county executive, the county council;
for a code county, the county commissioners or county council;
for a county commissioner county, the county commissioners; or
for a municipal corporation, the legislative body established by municipal charter.

"Governing body" includes:
the State, if the seizing authority is a unit of the State;
a county, if the seizing authority is a unit of a county;
a municipal corporation, if the seizing authority is a unit of a municipality; and
Baltimore City, if the seizing authority is the Police Department of Baltimore City.

section.section:
"Owner" includes:
a co-owner;
a life tenant;
a remainderman to a life tenancy in real property;
a holder of an inchoate interest in real property; and
a bona fide purchaser for value.

"Property" includes:
real property and anything growing on or attached to real property;
tangible and intangible personal property, including:
securities;
negotiable and nonnegotiable instruments;
vehicles and conveyances of any type;
privileges;
interests;
claims; and
rights;
an item, object, tool, substance, device, or weapon used in connection with a crime under the Controlled Dangerous Substances law; and
money.
